This point requires some explanation: FD's first volley (z3) was a lob; GM's first overhead (o2) was a jumping smash at such a steep vertical angle that it bounced and was just above head height on the rebound for FD to (lightly) hit is own reflex smash (o2) standing on the service line; FD's second volley (v3) was also a lob which GM finally managed to put away with yet another (this time much more emphatic) jumping overhead smash (o3*); as this very entertaining point demonstrates it is sometimes difficult to chart certain exchanges involving volleys of different nature (drop volley vs. lob vs. put-away) or whether overhead smashes are hit before or after the bounce
